text.text: Post a Remit containing multiple claims?

text:
To post a remit containing multiple claims, you can specify a different transaction number for each claim at the line-item level. You can also use the following steps:

1. Click the Transaction type field to select the transaction type from the list.
2. Enter a number that will identify the transaction in the Transaction number field.
3. Enter the date the payment was received in the Transaction date field.
4. Click the Allocate to claims button.

The system pulls up the invoices and displays them on the page.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=43rk9bdwda

text.text: How to Ignore Line Item?

text: To ignore a line item, you must first reverse the refund on the Claim page and then reverse the transaction. You can reverse a transaction because of insufficient funds, stopped payment, if it was posted in error. The entire transaction will reverse, this includes every single line item in the transaction.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=4nybou0ylq

text.text: Change a deposit date

text: You can change a deposit date on a posted transaction by following these steps: 1. Click the Payment posting tab. 2. Click the Change a deposit date on a posted transaction link. 3. Click the Change the Deposit Date on a Posted Transaction link. 4. Enter the new deposit date. 5. Click the Save button.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=sjtqi2fffq

text.text: How to Change a deposit date?

text: To change a deposit date on a posted transaction, you can follow these steps: 1. Click the Deposit date field. 2. Select a date. 3. Click Save. You can also reverse a transaction because of insufficient funds, stopped payment, if it was posted in error. The entire transaction will reverse, this includes every single line item in the transaction.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=sjtqi2fffq

text.text: How to Import Waystar 835 files?

text: Once the sFTP connection is established, Waystar will automatically download your remit files to ZOLL Billing in a nightly transmission. The imported files will appear in the morning in your Current tab on the Payments page. They will be easy to locate - their deposit date shows as "TBD". To work the imported claims: 1. Click TBD under the "Deposit date" column.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=vynky5pl50

text.text: Modifying charges on a Completed Claim

text: To modify charges on a completed claim, you can use the Charges tab. To do this, you can: Click the edit icon on the left side of the Charges tab Click inside the Add a charge field and select the mileage HCPCS from the list In the "Units" field, enter the mileage amount.
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=xpchr63ys3

text.text: How to use Itemized supplies?

text: To use Itemized supplies, you can: 1. Click Settings on the navigation bar 2. Click the Charges tab 3. Check the View field and verify that you are on the right charge category 4. If you are then click Itemize supplies
For more information click this : https://help.zollonline.com/billing/Content/Videos.htm?wchannelid=m8t21u1viq&wmediaid=6bsx0y73ks
